hwDHCPServerMib.name: hwDHCPServerMib

revisions.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing DHCP server, including objects used for DHCP server global pool, interface pool and informations of ip address used and conflicted in DHCP server, some Statistic informations about DHCP server

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolTable.description: DHCP Server Global Pool table for creating and deleting DHCP server global pool

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry.description: An entry in DHCP Server Global Pool table containing objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolName.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolName
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolName.description: DHCP server global pool name for creating or deleting DHCP server global pool

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows in this table, modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.Only three actions are used: active(1), createAndGo(4), destroy(6).While the hwDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus object is in the `createAndGo(4),The DHCP server global pool to be deleted must be exist

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.description: A table containing the configuration informations of DHCP server global pools, such as pool type, ip address, mask

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the network ip or host ip etc. to global pools for DHCP server

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolType.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolType
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolType.description: Type of a DHCP global pool. Any operations of this object will be bound with the operations of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork and hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask or with the operations of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr, hwDHCPSGlobalPoolMask and hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr. That means any operation of this object alone will be regarded as invalid operation. The value means: null(0)- It is a pool without ip address, host(1)- It is a pool with manual allocation, network(2)- It is a pool with automatic allocation

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork.description: Network ip address of a DHCP Server global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 1

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP Server global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP server global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.description: Host ip of a DHCP server global pool To detete a configured Host ip, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 2

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask.description: Host mask of a DHCP server global pool(host) The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a host ip of a DHCP server global pool was deleted, the Host mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP server global pool(host). To delete a configured hardware address, please set hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 3

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo operation for hwDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable Each value has the following meaning: undonetworkip(1): The value identifies the flag to delete a configured network ip undohostip(2): The value identifies the flag to delete a configured host ip undohosthaddr(3):The value identifies the flag to delete a configured hardware address invalid(4):The value is a default value,do nothing

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable.description: A table for configuring parameters to DHCP server global pool, include lease, Domain name,GateWayIP,DNSIP and so on

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for the configurations of parameters of DHCP server global pools

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay.description: A value which indicates number of days of the lease, The period over which a network address is allocated to a client is referred to as a 'lease'.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour.description: A value which indicates number of hours of the lease, The period over which a network address is allocated to a client is referred to as a 'lease'.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute.description: A value which indicates number of minutes of the lease, The period over which a network address is allocated to a client is referred to as a 'lease'.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited. The value means: invalid(0)- The lease of the network address that clients be assigned is finite, the period is decided by hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay,hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour and hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute unlimited(1)-The lease of the network address that clients be assigned is infinite

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolDomainName.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolDomainName
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolDomainName.description: Domain name for DHCP Clients, the domain name that client should use when resolving hostnames via the Domain Name System.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString.description: String of gateway ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip addresses can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip addresses at a time

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo.description: A gateway ip address to be deleted. This object is only for deleting a given ip address of gateway router

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip addresses can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip addresses at a time

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to be deleted. This object is only for deleting a given ip address of DNS server

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP Clients Each value has the following meaning: null(0)- no type designated bnode(1)- Broadcast ('B') nodes,Broadcast (or 'B') nodes communicate using a mix of UDP datagrams (both broadcast and directed) and TCP connections. pnode(2)- Point-to-point ('P') nodes,Point-to-point (or 'P') nodes communicate using only directed UDP datagrams and TCP sessions. mnode(4)- Mixed mode ('M') nodes,Mixed mode nodes (or 'M') nodes are P nodes which have been given certain B node characteristics. hnode(8)- Hybrid mode ('H') nodes.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString.description: String of NetBios server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip addresses can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip addresses at a time

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo.description: A NetBios server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip address of NetBios server

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaUndoFlag.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaUndoFlag
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo-operation for hwDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable Each value has the following meaning: undoDomain(1) - It means to delete Domain, undoLease(2) - It means to delete lease of a given ip address, undoGateway(3) - It means to delete a given ip address of gateway router, undoDns(4) - It means to delete a given ip address of DNS server, undoNbns(5) - It means to deletd a given ip address of NetBios server, undoNbType(6) - It means to delete NetBios node type , invalid(7) - The value is a default value,do nothing

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset.description: Reset the auto binding ip of the given global pool for DHCP server. The invalid(2) is a default vlaue, do nothing

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLogging.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLogging
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolLogging.description: Log the assigning IP addresses information of the given global pool for DHCP server.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionTable.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionTable
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options to DHCP server global pools, include option code type and value and so on

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionEntry.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionEntry
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring options to DHCP global pools

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionCode.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionCode
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionCode.description: Option code, All options begin with a tag octet, which uniquely identifies the option.

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionType.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionType
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionType.description: The object means option type in DHCP server global pool The value means : ascii(1)- The option type is ascii string hex(2) - The option type is hex number ip(3) - The option type is ip address cipher(4) - The option type is cipher string

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionHexString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionHexString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionHexString.description: Hex string of a option. 1 to 10 2 bytes or 4 bytes hex string can be configured at most simultaneously

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString.description: Ip string of a option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously

hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus.name: hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus
hwDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus.description: This object is used to configuration new rows in this table, modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.Only three actions are used: active(1), createAndGo(4), destroy(6). while configuration new option, you must specify option type and value

hwDHCPSGlobalTreeSiblingNodeName.name: hwDHCPSGlobalTreeSiblingNodeName

hwDHCPSInterfacePoolStaticBindEntry.description: An entry of objects for configuring static binding to DHCP interface pools. The index of this entry is the inIndex of ethernet

hwDHCPSIPInUseHAddr.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseHAddr
hwDHCPSIPInUseHAddr.description: The MAC addreess of host use the ip address in DHCP pools

hwDHCPSIPInUseIP.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseIP
hwDHCPSIPInUseIP.description: Ip address allocation to clients in DHCP pools

hwDHCPSIPInUseEndLease.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseEndLease
hwDHCPSIPInUseEndLease.description: End time of ip address leasese. The structure of the OCTET STRING is year/month/day:hour:munite:second -- YYYY/MM/DD:hh:mm:ss

hwDHCPSIPInUseType.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseType
hwDHCPSIPInUseType.description: Type of binding The value means manual(1) - manual allocation auto(2) - automatic allocation release(3)- The ip is automatic allocation,but it is already released offered(4)-The ip is offered to client

hwDHCPSIPInUsePoolName.name: hwDHCPSIPInUsePoolName
hwDHCPSIPInUsePoolName.description: Name of the DHCP server pool that allocated ip belongs to

hwDHCPSIPInUseInterface.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseInterface
hwDHCPSIPInUseInterface.description: Interface index information that ip address belong to

hwDHCPSIPInUseVlan.description: Vlan informationg that ip address belong to

hwDHCPSIPInUseAtmpvc.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseAtmpvc
hwDHCPSIPInUseAtmpvc.description: ATM Pvc informationg that ip address belong to

hwDHCPSForbiddenIPEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden ip to DHCP server

hwDHCPSForbiddenIPStart.description: Start ip address of forbidden ip

hwDHCPSConflictIPTable.name: hwDHCPSConflictIPTable
hwDHCPSConflictIPTable.description: A table for displaying the information of conflict ip for DHCP server,ip address is uesed by others when allocate the address.

hwDHCPSConflictIPEntry.name: hwDHCPSConflictIPEntry
hwDHCPSConflictIPEntry.description: An entry for displaying the information of conflict ip for DHCP server

hwDHCPSConflictIPType.name: hwDHCPSConflictIPType
hwDHCPSConflictIPType.description: Type of the detection of conflict ip, As a consistency check, the allocating server SHOULD probe the reused address before allocating the address, e.g., with ping or ARP

hwDHCPSConflictIPDetectTime.name: hwDHCPSConflictIPDetectTime
hwDHCPSConflictIPDetectTime.description: Time when the confict is detected. The structure of the OCTET STRING is year/month/day:hour:munite:second -- YYYY/MM/DD:hh:mm:ss

hwDHCPSServiceStatus.name: hwDHCPSServiceStatus
hwDHCPSServiceStatus.description: The status of DHCP service, The default value is disabled, which mean disabled the DHCP service; the other value is enabled, which mean enable the DHCP service

hwDHCPSDetectingServerStatus.name: hwDHCPSDetectingServerStatus
hwDHCPSDetectingServerStatus.description: The status of DHCP servers detecting function. If the value is enabled, It will check whether have other DHCP Servers. The default value is disabled

hwDHCPSPingNum.name: hwDHCPSPingNum
hwDHCPSPingNum.description: The number of ping packets sent out when check address conflict,the default value is 2.

hwDHCPSPingTimeout.name: hwDHCPSPingTimeout
hwDHCPSPingTimeout.description: The delay for the reply of a ping packet when check address conflict. Unit: millisecond, the default value is 500.

hwDHCPSWriteDataStatus.name: hwDHCPSWriteDataStatus
hwDHCPSWriteDataStatus.description: The status of the function writing data to the harddisk, It does not write data to the harddisk default, The information that written are the content that hwDHCPSConflictIPTable and hwDHCPSIPInUseTable, the default value is disable.

hwDHCPSWriteDataDirection.name: hwDHCPSWriteDataDirection
hwDHCPSWriteDataDirection.description: The directory of writing data to a harddisk, The format is directory and file name

hwDHCPSWriteDataDelay.name: hwDHCPSWriteDataDelay
hwDHCPSWriteDataDelay.description: The allowable delay of writing data to the harddisk. Unit: second,the default value is 300.

hwDHCPSWriteDataRecover.name: hwDHCPSWriteDataRecover
hwDHCPSWriteDataRecover.description: The flag used to recover DHCP data with the data on the harddisk,It means whether recover data from the data on the harddisk when system startup. The default value is disabled

hwDHCPSIPInUseResetIP.name: hwDHCPSIPInUseResetIP
hwDHCPSIPInUseResetIP.description: An ip in use that will be cleared. 0 returned for SET operation

hwDHCPSConflictIPResetIP.name: hwDHCPSConflictIPResetIP
hwDHCPSConflictIPResetIP.description: An conflict ip that will be cleared. 0 returned for SET operation

hwDHCPSIPResetFlag.name: hwDHCPSIPResetFlag
hwDHCPSIPResetFlag.description: A flag that descript the reset operation, 1 means deleting ip in use 2 means deleting conflict ip addresses
